--- USER ---
same error. water tile size fits the image but there is an offset between images

--- ASSISTANT ---
[Root cause: seamless texture periodic boundary condition broken. The 4D torus
mapping (cosine/sine wrapping) requires every noise octave period to exactly divide
the texture SIZE (128). Using a 2.3 multiplier as frequency breaks periodicity so
f(x+SIZE) ≠ f(x). Also, a single low-frequency octave (period=SIZE) produces one
dominant feature per tile, making each repetition individually recognizable.
Fix: use three octaves at periods SIZE/4=32, SIZE/8=16, SIZE/2=64 (all divide 128),
different seeds per octave. Regenerated water.png. World-space pattern transform
anchored via grassPattern.setTransform(new DOMMatrix([sc,0,0,sc, wo.x, wo.y]))
where wo = camera.worldToScreen(0,0) so all tiles share one continuous origin.]

