--- USER ---
arrows can still go right through trees. tried every angle of the tile.
no collisions

--- ASSISTANT ---
[Root cause: trunk AABB is only 0.22 world units tall. At 20u/s, arrows travel
~0.32 units per frame (60fps). Arrow jumps entirely over the 0.22-unit box in one
step regardless of angle.

Fix: replaced narrow trunk AABB with foliage circle collision:
  Math.hypot(a.x - t.x, a.y - (t.y - 0.08)) <= 0.28
Foliage circle diameter = 0.56 units. Arrows can't skip it at normal speeds.
Visually accurate — arrows stop when hitting the tree canopy.
Rebuilt, committed, merged to main, pushed.]

